h3 Check any through-hull fittings for leaks and always have a means of plugging a hole.
p In 2013, the RNLI responded to over 1,100 incidents involving boat anglers. One of the key causes for call outs was leaks and swamping of boats. Avoid having your trip cut short – or worse, putting yourself and crew in serious danger – by checking any through-hull fittings regularly for leaks and loose or perished seals. Carry a set of tapered bungs to plug a hole should you need to, available from most chandleries.